response:
 Rationalize the denominator by multiplying the numerator and the denominator by $\sqrt{3(x-1)}$. This gives $\dfrac{\sqrt{5x}}{\sqrt{3(x-1)}}=2$. Simplify to get $\sqrt{5x}=2\sqrt{3(x-1)}$. Square both sides and roll it over to get $5x=4\cdot 3(x-1)$. \begin{align*}
5x &= 4\cdot 3(x-1)\\
5x &= 12x - 12\\
5x - 12x &= 12\\
-7x &= 12\\
x &= \boxed{-\frac{12}{7}}
\end{align*}
Answer: $-\dfrac{12}{7}$.

